{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]For many long years I've played a lone hand
[G7]I rode my horse in many strange [C]lands
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Until one day I stopped for awhile
[G7]For two blue eyes and a sunny [C]smile
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]So howl away you old [C]coyote
[G7]I hear your sad and lonesome [C]song
[F]You're calling me back to old [C]Montana
[G7]Back to those hills where I [C]belong
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
